Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the #oven{} is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @breadcrumbs{10%grams}, half the @wholegrain mustard{17%grams} and the @salt{¼%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British beef mince{240%grams}. Season with pepper and mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a large baking tray. Bake on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Pop a large #frying pan{} on medium heat and melt in the @butter{20%grams}.

Once melted, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}. Add the @sugar{1%tsp} and half the @cider vinegar{15%milliliter}.

Cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine the @sugar{¼%tsp} and @olive oil{½%tbsp} for the dressing and the remaining cider vinegar. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then set your dressing aside.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%grams}.

Once the burgers are cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of them and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, pop the @sliced burger buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

In a small bowl, mix the remaining mustard with the @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}.

Just before everything's ready, toss the @baby leaf mix{20%grams} in the dressing.

When everything's ready, spread the mustard mayo over the bun bases. Top the bases with a cheesy burger and the caramelised onion, then sandwich shut with the bun lids. Serve the fries and baby leaf salad alongside. Enjoy!